------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to run:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) Type the following command to run 'script.sh':

$ ./script.sh
192.168.1.2    == 255.255.255.0
127.0.0.1      == 255.0.0.0
10.0.3.1       == 255.255.255.0

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Notes:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) In some systems 'ifconfig' may require root permissions. In this case the
   script shall be run under 'root'.

2) The output of the 'script.sh' depends on network settings.

3) Script was tested in Ubuntu 12.04.

